{'text': 'Today is the Non-Profit Connections Virtual Career Fair! Thank you to all of the organizations participating. Students: make sure to register for the fair on Handshake.'}

{'text': 'HAPPENING TODAY!

Social Good through Public Finance and Wealth Management
Friday, March 12th
12-1pm ET
Register via Handshake

Join us for a candid conversation with MSPPM alums Jenai Booker and Shawneil Campbell, from the class of 2015. In this conversation they aim to do three things: (1) Demystify preconceived notions about the fields of Public Finance and Wealth Management; (2) Illustrate how to get the most out of your MSPPM degree; and (3) Network with all of you. We look forward to a fruitful conversation.'}

{'text': 'Today kicks off the @heinzcollege Washington DC Colloquium! The Washington DC Colloquium is an annual Heinz College event that aims to educate students on different industries and sectors in Washington DC, while engaging with our Heinz College alumni network.'}

{'text': 'Network Nationally continues today! Register and log in to the event to live chat with over 40 alumni from all degree programs hosting virtual booths. Thanks to all the Alumni, Students, and Staff that make these events possible!'}

{'text': 'Calling all Heinz College of Information Systems and Public Policy Alumni & Students!

Virtually meet and network with alumni from various industry sectors all around the country.  Alumni will host virtual booths in the InfernoAR platform and will represent all of the various Heinz Programs. Join a live chat by reviewing the schedule and the booth information that includes alumni names, programs, graduation years, job titles, current company and brief bios.
Once you are logged into Network Nationally you will also have the opportunity for real time text chats taking place among all Event Attendees who jump in on Thursday & Friday so be sure to create an Attendee Profile to participate!

‚Ä¢ Register for Network Nationally: link on Facebook
‚Ä¢ Please complete a Profile so you show up as an event Attendee
‚Ä¢ Log into the Network Nationally event page frequently from Thur Oct. 22 to Fri. Oct. 23 so you can have text chats with other alumni, current students & Heinz staff!! Check out our Heinz College Program Chat rooms and join the Fun!!!'}

{'text': 'Destinations in Data - happening THIS WEEK! \nA three-day virtual event for @heinzcollege students to learn how Data Analytics skills can be applied in various industries such as Technology, E-commerce, Healthcare, Public Tech, & Entertainment. Attendees will have the opportunity to establish current Heinz College student connections by visiting virtual student showcase booths, hear from Heinz alumni and industry leaders, and see corporate recruiters who want to hire Heinz students for data analytics jobs and internships!'}

{'text': 'With the current #computerchip shortage in the spotlight, #cmuece is preparing the chip workforce of the future by attracting students to the integrated circuit design field. \n\nCMU established an initiative with industry partners whereby they fund scholarships and fellowships for students who follow the path of a hardware concentration. Companies recognize that providing a financial incentive toward hardware design is needed to give students the opportunity to consider that option. Additionally, the industry partners share tangible demonstrations of what such careers look like, and what exciting opportunities await them.'}

{'text': 'Esther Bedoyan, a junior majoring ECE and biomedical engineering with a minor in Chinese studies, has received the prestigious 2021 Barry Goldwater Scholarship to encourage her pursuit of a research career.

Since the fall of 2020, Bedoyan has been conducting research in Dr. Maysam Chamanzar‚Äôs lab focusing on developing an adaptive frequency domain filtering technique that removes electrical interference from electrophysiology data.

‚ÄúI‚Äôve had a lot of fun with this project. I‚Äôve been able to independently develop this filtering technique and test its performance on real electrophysiology recordings collected from neural organoids and present my findings at multiple conferences and poster presentations,‚Äù Bedoyan said.

Upon graduation, she plans on completing the Integrated Masters Bachelor Program at CMU, then pursuing a Ph.D.

#goldwaterscholarship #engineer #cmuece @carnegiemellon @cmuengineering'}

{'text': 'Giulia Fanti and Brandon Lucia are recipients of the 2021 Sloan Research Fellowship. The fellowships, awarded annually since 1955, honor early career scholars whose achievements put them among the very best scientific minds working today. Winners receive a two-year, $75,000 fellowship to further their research.
.
"They are already recognized as stars in their respective research communities and I am honored to have them as members of our ECE department and CMU community." - Larry Pileggi, department head of electrical and computer engineering. 
.
#SloanFellow'}

{'text': 'Congratulations to the recent #cmuece professorships! As the highest academic award a university can bestow on a faculty member, professorships are reserved for those who show continued contributions in their field. #engineers'}

{'text': 'Alumnus Jeff Mullen (ECE ‚Äò00, Tepper ‚Äò09) and his company, Dynamics Inc., have created an innovative way to inactivate coronavirus in the air. \n\nNanowave Air uses ultraviolet light to inactivate the virus‚Äîthat is, it damages the virus until it can no longer replicate. In May, Dynamics was the first to demonstrate inactivation using UV light. Then, they performed a series of experiments to figure out the best way to fight the virus. These experiments involved surfaces, liquids, and the air we breathe. In general, UV light is relatively weak. A long exposure is required to inactivate the virus, so it is usually only used for surfaces.'}
